  </div>
  <div class="dir-rationale">
    <b>Why this works</b>
    A 3×2 grid of equal-weight cards, ruled like a printed index. Each card carries an archetype number, axis tag, name, one-line definition, two differentiators, and a nearby neighbor — nothing else. No fingerprint chart on the card; that detail lives one click away in the AI Field Guide. The flatness is the point: every archetype gets the same air, so scanning is a horizontal sweep across uniform cells rather than a comparison between unequal posters.
  </div>

