          </ol>
          <div class="legend">
            <b>What this page is</b>
            An explainer. No score, no archetype produced. To get an archetype, take the AI Governance Compass.
          </div>
        </aside>

        <div class="d2-content">

          <!-- §1 axes -->
          <section>
            <h2 class="sec"><span class="num">§1</span>The eight axes</h2>
            <p class="sec-deck">The vocabulary the Atlas uses. Names and opposing poles only — no positions.</p>
            <div class="d2-axes-list">
              <div class="d2-axis">
                <div class="n">A1</div>
                <div class="body"><div class="nm">Public oversight</div><div class="desc">How much accountability is required before deployment.</div></div>
                <div class="poles"><div class="row"><span>DELEGATION</span><span>—</span><span>OVERSIGHT</span></div><div class="scale"></div></div>
              </div>
              <div class="d2-axis">
                <div class="n">A2</div>
                <div class="body"><div class="nm">Capability pace</div><div class="desc">How aggressively to advance frontier capability against risk.</div></div>
                <div class="poles"><div class="row"><span>SLOW</span><span>—</span><span>PUSH</span></div><div class="scale"></div></div>
              </div>
              <div class="d2-axis">
                <div class="n">A3</div>
                <div class="body"><div class="nm">Openness</div><div class="desc">Default toward release of weights, data, and methods.</div></div>
                <div class="poles"><div class="row"><span>CLOSED</span><span>—</span><span>OPEN</span></div><div class="scale"></div></div>
              </div>
              <div class="d2-axis">
                <div class="n">A4</div>
                <div class="body"><div class="nm">Concentration</div><div class="desc">Tolerance for a few labs holding most frontier capability.</div></div>
                <div class="poles"><div class="row"><span>DIFFUSE</span><span>—</span><span>CONCENTRATED</span></div><div class="scale"></div></div>
              </div>
              <div class="d2-axis">
                <div class="n">A5</div>
                <div class="body"><div class="nm">Legitimacy &amp; rule-setting</div><div class="desc">Where governance authority is grounded.</div></div>
                <div class="poles"><div class="row"><span>PROCEDURAL</span><span>—</span><span>SUBSTANTIVE</span></div><div class="scale"></div></div>
              </div>
              <div class="d2-axis">
                <div class="n">A6</div>
                <div class="body"><div class="nm">Competition vs coordination</div><div class="desc">How much to read AI as state competition vs shared problem.</div></div>
                <div class="poles"><div class="row"><span>COORDINATE</span><span>—</span><span>COMPETE</span></div><div class="scale"></div></div>
              </div>
              <div class="d2-axis">
                <div class="n">A7</div>
                <div class="body"><div class="nm">Harm centering</div><div class="desc">Whose harms count first when tradeoffs appear.</div></div>
                <div class="poles"><div class="row"><span>AGGREGATE</span><span>—</span><span>CONCENTRATED</span></div><div class="scale"></div></div>
              </div>
              <div class="d2-axis">
                <div class="n">A8</div>
                <div class="body"><div class="nm">Instruments</div><div class="desc">Whether rules act through individual rights or industrial policy.</div></div>
                <div class="poles"><div class="row"><span>RIGHTS</span><span>—</span><span>INDUSTRIAL</span></div><div class="scale"></div></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- §2 parts ways -->
          <section>
            <h2 class="sec"><span class="num">§2</span>Where nearby archetypes part ways</h2>
            <p class="sec-deck">Pairs whose fingerprints overlap; the split is what tells them apart.</p>
            <div class="d2-parts-row head">
              <div>Pair</div>
              <div>What they share</div>
              <div>Where they split</div>
            </div>
            <div class="d2-parts-row">
              <div class="pair">Guardrailist · Risk Steward<small>Pair A</small></div>
              <div class="col"><b>shared</b>High oversight; suspicion of frontier-only safety claims.</div>
              <div class="col"><b>split</b>Procedural legitimacy &amp; institutions vs concentrated harms &amp; standing for affected publics.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="d2-parts-row">
              <div class="pair">Strategic Competitor · Industrial Statist<small>Pair B</small></div>
              <div class="col"><b>shared</b>State-level reading of AI; tolerant of capability concentration.</div>
              <div class="col"><b>split</b>Capability edge framing vs procurement / subsidy / standards instruments.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="d2-parts-row">
              <div class="pair">Open Ecosystem · Risk Steward<small>Pair C</small></div>
              <div class="col"><b>shared</b>Worry about concentration of frontier capability.</div>
              <div class="col"><b>split</b>Default to release as cure vs standing and remedy for affected groups.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="d2-parts-row">
              <div class="pair">Multilateral · Guardrailist<small>Pair D</small></div>
              <div class="col"><b>shared</b>Want enforceable rules; skeptical of voluntary commitments alone.</div>
              <div class="col"><b>split</b>Outward to regimes and standards bodies vs inward to domestic accountability.</div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- §3 cross-read -->
          <section>
            <h2 class="sec"><span class="num">§3</span>How IR and AI cross-read</h2>
            <p class="sec-deck">Three meeting points between the IR Foundation and the AI Compass. The two are related layers, not parallel assessments.</p>
            <div class="d2-cross">
              <div class="d2-cross-cell">
                <div class="ir">IR concept</div>
                <h5>Legitimacy of rule-setting</h5>
                <p class="desc">In IR, the question is whether legitimacy is procedural (right process) or substantive (right outcomes), and across whose regimes.</p>
                <div class="ai"><b>AI:</b> Who has standing to audit a model, and on what authority?</div>
              </div>
              <div class="d2-cross-cell">
                <div class="ir">IR concept</div>
                <h5>Security dilemma</h5>
                <p class="desc">In IR, competition can be self-fulfilling — defensive moves read as offensive, escalation follows.</p>
                <div class="ai"><b>AI:</b> Pace pressure can be invoked or actual; the Field Guide names which is which.</div>
